@startuml activity-data-missing
' Why absence of activity data is not evidence of inactivity: silence vs unknown vs unreachable.
' Source of truth: docs/src/controller/hibernation-and-wake.md
!include _style.puml

start
:activity fan-out returns
(GET /v1/activity, one call
per gateway Pod IP);<<$gwBg>>

if (any replica reachable?) then (no)
  :UNREACHABLE
  preserve the current phase
  set GatewayReachable=False
  requeue with backoff;<<$mutedBg>>
  stop
else (yes: use the reachable ones)
endif

:per reachable replica, compare its\nreplicaStartedAt against the Agent's\nstatus.phaseTransitionTime;

if (replicaStartedAt is the more recent?) then (yes)
  :UNKNOWN
  the replica restarted while the
  Agent was Running, so its empty
  store is not evidence of silence;<<$mutedBg>>
else (no)
  :SILENCE
  the replica covered the whole
  period and recorded no activity;<<$agentBg>>
endif

if (all replicas unknown?) then (yes)
  :defer, no idle or\nhibernation transition;<<$mutedBg>>
  stop
else (no)
endif

if (has some replica been up\nfor at least idleTimeout?) then (no)
  :defer, no idle or\nhibernation transition;<<$mutedBg>>
  stop
else (yes)
endif

:missing data may now be read\nas genuine inactivity;
:merge: most recent timestamp\nper agent across replicas;
:then filter on\nspec.lifecycle.activitySource\n(gatewayTraffic, agentHeartbeat, both);
:evaluate Running -> Idle -> Hibernating;<<$ctrlBg>>
stop

note right
  Merge across replicas first,
  then filter.
  ....
  Operational consequence: after a
  synchronized gateway rollout no
  replica has been up for
  idleTimeout, so every idle and
  hibernation transition is
  deferred for idleTimeout.
end note

@enduml
